Here's the Java code for performing spectral clustering:


```java
import org.apache.commons.math3.linear.RealMatrix;
import org.apache.commons.math3.linear.EigenDecomposition;
import org.apache.commons.math3.linear.MatrixUtils;
import org.apache.commons.math3.ml.clustering.Clusterable;
import org.apache.commons.math3.ml.clustering.SpectralClusterer;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class SpectralClustering {

 public static void main(String[] args) {

 List<String> sequences = new ArrayList<>();
 sequences.add("ATCGATCG");
 sequences.add("GCTAGCTA");
 sequences.add("CGATCGAT");
 sequences.add("ATCGCGAT");
 sequences.add("CGATCGTA");

 // convert sequences to a matrix of pairwise distances
 RealMatrix distances = MatrixUtils.createRealMatrix(sequences.size(), sequences.size());
 for (int i = 0; i < sequences.size(); i++) {
 for (int j = 0; j < sequences.size(); j++) {
 int distance = 0;
 for (int k = 0; k < sequences.get(i).length(); k++) {
 if (sequences.get(i).charAt(k) != sequences.get(j).charAt(k)) {
 distance++;
 }
 }
 distances.setEntry(i, j, distance);
 }
 }

 // perform spectral clustering
 SpectralClusterer<String> clusterer = new SpectralClusterer<>(2, 10);
 List<? extends Clusterable> points = new ArrayList<>();
 for (String seq : sequences) {
 points.add(new SequenceClusterable(seq));
 }
 List<List<Clusterable>> clusters = clusterer.cluster(points, distances);

 // print the cluster assignments for each sequence
 for (int i = 0; i < sequences.size(); i++) {
 for (int j = 0; j < clusters.size(); j++) {
 if (clusters.get(j).contains(points.get(i))) {
 System.out.println("Sequence " + (i + 1) + " assigned to cluster " + (j + 1));
 break;
 }
 }
 }
 }

 private static class SequenceClusterable implements Clusterable {

 private final String sequence;

 public SequenceClusterable(String sequence) {
 this.sequence = sequence;
 }

 @Override
 public double[] getPoint() {
 double[] point = new double[sequence.length()];
 for (int i = 0; i < sequence.length(); i++) {
 if (sequence.charAt(i) == 'A') {
 point[i] = 1;
 } else {
 point[i] = 0;
 }
 }
 return point;
 }
 }
}
```
Note that the Java code for spectral clustering uses the Apache Commons Math library, which provides various linear algebra and clustering algorithms. The `RealMatrix` class is used to represent the pairwise distance matrix, and the `SpectralClusterer` class is used to perform the clustering. The `SequenceClusterable` class is a custom implementation of the `Clusterable` interface, which is used to convert the sequence data into a format that can be processed by the clustering algorithm.

